16namespace webrtc {
17
18///////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
19// enum ACMVADMode
20// An enumerator for aggressiveness of VAD
21// -VADNormal : least aggressive mode.
22// -VADLowBitrate : more aggressive than "VADNormal" to save on
23// bit-rate.
24// -VADAggr : an aggressive mode.
25// -VADVeryAggr : the most agressive mode.
26//
27enum ACMVADMode {
28 VADNormal = 0,
29 VADLowBitrate = 1,
30 VADAggr = 2,
31 VADVeryAggr = 3
32};
33
34enum class AudioFrameType {
35 kEmptyFrame = 0,
36 kAudioFrameSpeech = 1,
37 kAudioFrameCN = 2,
38};
39
40///////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
41//
42// Enumeration of Opus mode for intended application.
43//
44// kVoip : optimized for voice signals.
45// kAudio : optimized for non-voice signals like music.
46//
47enum OpusApplicationMode {
48 kVoip = 0,
49 kAudio = 1,
50};
51
52// Statistics for calls to AudioCodingModule::PlayoutData10Ms().
53struct AudioDecodingCallStats {
54 AudioDecodingCallStats()
55 : calls_to_silence_generator(0),
56 calls_to_neteq(0),
57 decoded_normal(0),
58 decoded_neteq_plc(0),
59 decoded_codec_plc(0),
60 decoded_cng(0),
61 decoded_plc_cng(0),
62 decoded_muted_output(0) {}
63
64 int calls_to_silence_generator; // Number of calls where silence generated,
65 // and NetEq was disengaged from decoding.
66 int calls_to_neteq; // Number of calls to NetEq.
67 int decoded_normal; // Number of calls where audio RTP packet decoded.
68 int decoded_neteq_plc; // Number of calls resulted in NetEq PLC.
69 int decoded_codec_plc; // Number of calls resulted in codec PLC.
70 int decoded_cng; // Number of calls where comfort noise generated due to DTX.
71 int decoded_plc_cng; // Number of calls resulted where PLC faded to CNG.
72 int decoded_muted_output; // Number of calls returning a muted state output.
73};
74
75// NETEQ statistics.
76struct NetworkStatistics {
77 // current jitter buffer size in ms
78 uint16_t currentBufferSize;
79 // preferred (optimal) buffer size in ms
80 uint16_t preferredBufferSize;
81 // adding extra delay due to "peaky jitter"
82 bool jitterPeaksFound;
83 // Stats below correspond to similarly-named fields in the WebRTC stats spec.
84 // https://w3c.github.io/webrtc-stats/#dom-rtcmediastreamtrackstats
85 uint64_t totalSamplesReceived;
86 uint64_t concealedSamples;
87 uint64_t silentConcealedSamples;
88 uint64_t concealmentEvents;
89 uint64_t jitterBufferDelayMs;
90 uint64_t jitterBufferEmittedCount;
91 // Non standard stats propagated to spec complaint GetStats API.
92 uint64_t jitterBufferTargetDelayMs;
93 uint64_t insertedSamplesForDeceleration;
94 uint64_t removedSamplesForAcceleration;
95 uint64_t fecPacketsReceived;
96 uint64_t fecPacketsDiscarded;
97 // Stats below DO NOT correspond directly to anything in the WebRTC stats
98 // fraction (of original stream) of synthesized audio inserted through
99 // expansion (in Q14)
100 uint16_t currentExpandRate;
101 // fraction (of original stream) of synthesized speech inserted through
102 // expansion (in Q14)
103 uint16_t currentSpeechExpandRate;
104 // fraction of synthesized speech inserted through pre-emptive expansion
105 // (in Q14)
106 uint16_t currentPreemptiveRate;
107 // fraction of data removed through acceleration (in Q14)
108 uint16_t currentAccelerateRate;
109 // fraction of data coming from secondary decoding (in Q14)
110 uint16_t currentSecondaryDecodedRate;
111 // Fraction of secondary data, including FEC and RED, that is discarded (in
112 // Q14). Discarding of secondary data can be caused by the reception of the
113 // primary data, obsoleting the secondary data. It can also be caused by early
114 // or late arrival of secondary data.
115 uint16_t currentSecondaryDiscardedRate;
116 // average packet waiting time in the jitter buffer (ms)
117 int meanWaitingTimeMs;
118 // max packet waiting time in the jitter buffer (ms)
119 int maxWaitingTimeMs;
120 // count of the number of buffer flushes
121 uint64_t packetBufferFlushes;
122 // number of samples expanded due to delayed packets
123 uint64_t delayedPacketOutageSamples;
124 // arrival delay of incoming packets
125 uint64_t relativePacketArrivalDelayMs;
126 // number of audio interruptions
127 int32_t interruptionCount;
128 // total duration of audio interruptions
129 int32_t totalInterruptionDurationMs;
130};
131
132} // namespace webrtc
